24. Key Forensic Workflow

Step-by-step
	1.	Identify system
	•	/etc/os-release
	2.	Identify users
	•	/etc/passwd
	•	/etc/group
	3.	Check privileges
	•	/etc/sudoers
	4.	Analyze logs
	•	/var/log/auth.log
	•	/var/log/syslog
	5.	Check persistence
	•	cron
	•	services
	•	bashrc
	6.	Review activity
	•	bash_history
	•	viminfo
	7.	Check network
	•	ip a
	•	netstat
	8.	Investigate applications
	•	/var/log/apache2

⸻

25. Core Analyst Questions

Always ask:
	•	Who logged in?
	•	When did it happen?
	•	What commands were executed?
	•	Did privilege escalation occur?
	•	What persistence exists?
	•	Any external connections?
	•	Any suspicious files?

